WEBVTT

00:04.992 --> 00:14.871
I don't like the

00:04.992 --> 00:14.871
intro. Okay, we were talking about the philosophy 
of examining boards and protection of the public

00:14.891 --> 00:22.225
and the Federal Trade Commission practice rules 
and so forth. What's your general attitude toward

00:27.091 --> 00:35.004
the philosophy of whether or not examining boards 
really are in the best interest of the public?

00:43.758 --> 00:49.107
I feel that the duty and responsibility of the 
board is to protect the public. That's

00:53.633 --> 01:11.131
basically the main reason that the board exists is 
not for any other reason except to protect the

00:53.633 --> 01:11.131
public. And in examining these applicants,

01:19.613 --> 01:47.646
It's difficult to

01:19.613 --> 01:47.646
visualize, so to speak, but I think it's the 
responsibility of the board to not figure out

01:19.613 --> 01:47.646
necessarily who is the most capable individual

01:51.271 --> 02:04.923
taking examination, but how far can we go with an 
individual and let him have a license and he won't

01:51.271 --> 02:04.923
be a danger to the public? See what I'm talking 
about? Instead of eliminating

02:08.407 --> 02:19.877
them or figuring out which one is the best, we try to 
figure out How sorry can a man be and still not be a

02:19.992 --> 02:27.403
danger to the public? It creates a problem. I saw an 
editorial in the American Animal Hospital

02:29.586 --> 02:33.171
Journal the other day. It was... I don't know 
whether it was an editorial or a letter to the

02:36.636 --> 02:39.260
editor. Of course, there is some difference 
between those two. But the statement made in the

02:43.826 --> 02:48.413
journal was... that he looked in the not too far 
distant future for the only thing for an examining

02:49.270 --> 03:11.020
board to do, if they had a diploma from a legitimate 
veterinary school, that they were obligated to

02:49.270 --> 03:11.020
let him practice anywhere, anytime. Do you think 
that time may be coming? I would hope not. I think

03:16.388 --> 03:19.578
that there should be some changes. I feel that

03:20.140 --> 03:29.470
we should examine on a regional basis rather than 
just a state. Possibly Arkansas, Louisiana,

03:29.905 --> 03:41.236
Texas, Oklahoma, and even New Mexico could band 
together and have an examination. And if I pass

03:41.997 --> 03:46.821
that examination, I can practice in any of those 
states. It probably never will come. I have some

03:50.064 --> 03:53.768
ideas about education, too. I

03:53.788 --> 03:59.153
don't know why I bring it up at this time, but I 
firmly believe that our educational process

03:59.977 --> 04:16.551
would be better utilized if we had an interchange 
of students from these various veterinary

04:17.037 --> 04:21.185
schools. Three or four students from Texas could 
go to Iowa, and three or four from Iowa could go to

04:22.007 --> 04:33.710
Washington, and three or four from Washington go 
to Cornell, intermingle them. Then those kids

04:33.730 --> 04:36.295
would come back home You know, every institution 
is strong in different areas. And they could bring

04:42.805 --> 04:48.092
information back from Iowa that would be 
beneficial to the state of Texas. And we could take

04:48.653 --> 04:59.048
information from Texas or background material 
from Texas and it would be beneficial to these

04:48.653 --> 04:59.048
other schools. And why they don't do it, I don't 
know. But back to this matter of examination, I

05:02.633 --> 05:23.292
think that this

05:02.633 --> 05:23.292
matter of a degree, of a diploma from a school, 
doesn't...

05:24.757 --> 05:46.400
qualify you to practice, say, in Texas because you 
may have a background, a moral background that's

05:24.757 --> 05:46.400
not suitable, a type of person that we wouldn't 
want to practice in Texas, even though you had a

05:24.757 --> 05:46.400
fine record from the school that you come from.

05:49.663 --> 05:52.266
That would be the... The main reason that I would 
see to not just accept them on a diploma. We have had

05:59.775 --> 06:21.257
graduates from A&M College

05:59.775 --> 06:21.257
that

05:59.775 --> 06:21.257
really, and I'm sure other schools have too, that 
