Worth, we had the so-called X disease problem,

11:57.168 --> 12:10.020
chlorinated naphthalene poisoning. We didn't 
know what it was, and Dr. Smith had come up to see me,

12:10.040 --> 12:25.875
and we'd have anywhere from one to two to several in 
a herd involved, and he'd take cultures, and he'd

12:10.040 --> 12:25.875
look, and he'd do this, that, and the other, and 
then... About 1951 or 1952,

12:26.716 --> 12:42.590
we had an outbreak of X disease, and catalept was 
traced to cottonseed cake. They had... They had

12:45.076 --> 12:56.534
sucked all the normal oils out of that cake and then 
used mineral oil, incorporated mineral oil into

12:45.076 --> 12:56.534
that meal so that it would cake, see? So they could 
make a cake. And this particular mineral oil had

12:58.337 --> 13:11.037
chlorinated naphthalene in it, which is a product 
that's used to make oils stronger and more durable

12:58.337 --> 13:11.037
in machinery, see? But it doesn't work very good in 
cattle. But that was a big problem and a big

13:13.240 --> 13:16.705
headache to us. And when that was finally found 
out, I remember Dr. Smith was up here one day

13:16.725 --> 13:28.883
talking to us after we'd found out what caused the X 
disease and all. And he was talking to the head of

13:29.564 --> 13:34.812
the Trader's Oil mill out here. He was in the crowd. 
And he said, we... had worked for years trying to

13:42.569 --> 13:47.774
figure out what caused this X disease. And then 
this Trader's oil mill provides us with this

13:48.174 --> 13:52.778
wonderful experiment. It was millions of dollars 
that cost Trader's. But we found that out. And we

13:57.923 --> 14:06.351
stopped the recurrence of X disease by removing 
that. There used to be in old tractor oils and

14:07.112 --> 14:09.554
greases. And those cattle would get out and lick on 
it. And you've probably seen it in your practice.

14:16.022 --> 14:21.628
